{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Don't it seem to rain a lot in our [F]lives
[G7]Those dark clouds always seems to hide our blue [C]skies
[F]But this Texas sun has burned its way right through my brain
[G7]Now my job is done and hard times follow just like [C]rain
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]California seems to be the place to go
[G7]Dreams out there come true they say and turn to [C]gold
[F]But our California dreams turned out to be just lies
[G7]Don't it seem to rain a lot in our [C]lives
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]But somewhere we'll find new dreams and sunshine
[G7]Green fields and blue skies where blue birds [C]fly
[F]Where the only rain is a summer shower to cool the nights
[G7]Yes somewhere there's new dreams and [C]sunshine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
